object.script:
local out_per_launch = property.getNumber("Outputs per launch (for example, 1 for a missile, 4 for a missile pod)") local current_launch_number = 0
local limit_behaviour = property.getBool("Limit Reached Behaviour")
local hold = property.getBool("Press or Hold Output")
function onTick() local total_launches = input.getNumber(1) local launch = input.getBool(1) if launch and total_launches * out_per_launch > current_launch_number then if not hold then output.setBool(math.ceil(current_launch_number/out_per_launch), false) end output.setNumber(1, 0) current_launch_number = current_launch_number + 1 output.setBool(math.ceil(current_launch_number/out_per_launch), true) else if limit_behvaiour then current_launch_number = 0 else output.setNumber(1, 1) end end end

object.script:
local left_max = property.getNumber("Left Torpedo Max Angle") local left_min = property.getNumber("Left Torpedo Min Angle")
local right_max = property.getNumber("Right Torpedo Max Angle") local right_min = property.getNumber("Right Torpedo Min Angle")
function getAngle(tx, tz, px, pz) return math.deg(math.atan(px - tx, pz - tz)) end
function onTick() local pos_x = input.getNumber(1) local pos_z = input.getNumber(2)
local dest_x = input.getNumber(3) local dest_z = input.getNumber(4)
local pos_angle = input.getNumber(5)*-360
local dest_angle = getAngle(pos_x, pos_z, dest_x, dest_z)
local angle_diff = dest_angle - pos_angle
output.setNumber(1, angle_diff)
if angle_diff >= left_min and angle_diff <= left_max then output.setBool(1, true) else output.setBool(1, false) end
if angle_diff >= right_min and angle_diff <= right_max then output.setBool(2, true) else output.setBool(2, false) end end

object.script:
old_left_input = false old_right_input = false
left_bias = true
function onTick() local left_input = input.getBool(1) local right_input = input.getBool(2)
local left_output = false local right_output = false
if left_input and not right_input and left_input ~= old_left_input then -- only left left_output = true elseif not left_input and right_input and right_input ~= old_right_input then -- only right right_output = true elseif left_input and right_input and left_input ~= old_left_input and right_input ~= old_right_input then -- both if left_bias then left_output = true else right_output = true end left_bias = not left_bias end
output.setBool(1, left_output) output.setBool(2, right_output)
old_left_input = left_input old_right_input = right_input end

object.script:
-- made by Toastery
fade_in_time = property.getNumber("Fade In (s)") ~= 0 and property.getNumber("Fade In (s)")*60 or 0.01 fade_out_time = property.getNumber("Fade Out (s)") ~= 0 and property.getNumber("Fade Out (s)")*60 or 0.01
init_values = { on = false, r = 0, g = 0, b = 0 }
last = init_values
start = init_values
tar = init_values
new = init_values
function onTick() cur = { on = input.getBool(1), r = input.getBool(1) and input.getNumber(1)/255 or 0, g = input.getBool(1) and input.getNumber(2)/255 or 0, b = input.getBool(1) and input.getNumber(3)/255 or 0 }
if tar.on ~= cur.on or tar.r ~= cur.r or tar.g ~= cur.g or tar.b ~= cur.b then tar = cur start = last end
if tar ~= last then
new = { on = cur.on, r = last.r < cur.r and math.clamp(last.r + (tar.r - start.r)/fade_in_time, 0, tar.r) or math.clamp(last.r + (tar.r - start.r)/fade_out_time, tar.r, 1), g = last.g < cur.g and math.clamp(last.g + (tar.g - start.g)/fade_in_time, 0, tar.g) or math.clamp(last.g + (tar.g - start.g)/fade_out_time, tar.g, 1), b = last.b < cur.b and math.clamp(last.b + (tar.b - start.b)/fade_in_time, 0, tar.b) or math.clamp(last.b + (tar.b - start.b)/fade_out_time, tar.b, 1), }
last = new end output.setBool(1, new.on) output.setNumber(1, new.r) output.setNumber(2, new.g) output.setNumber(3, new.b) end
function math.clamp(x, min, max) return max<x and max or min>x and min or x end

object.script:
pi = math.pi pi2 = math.pi*2
function onTick()
curX = input.getNumber(3) curY = input.getNumber(4)
targetX = input.getNumber(1) targetY = input.getNumber(2)
compass = input.getNumber(5)
bearing = compass*-pi2
frontx=math.sin(bearing)*15000+curX fronty=math.cos(bearing)*15000+curY
distance=((targetX-curX)^2 + (targetY-curY)^2)^.5
output.setNumber(1, distance)
output.setNumber(2, frontx) output.setNumber(3, fronty) end

lasttargetcoords={0,0,0} lasttargetcoords1={0,0,0} targetcoords={0,0,0} lastmissilecoords={0,0,0} last_vertical_los=0 last_horizontal_los=0 delta_delta_vlos=0 delta_delta_hlos=0 pitch=0 yaw=0 last_acceleration_vlos = 0 last_acceleration_hlos = 0 function onTick() missileRadarPitchAngle=input.getNumber(1)*math.pi*2 missileRadarYawAngle=input.getNumber(2)*math.pi*2 missileRadarDistance=input.getNumber(3) missileGPSX=input.getNumber(4) missileGPSY=input.getNumber(5) missileAltitude=input.getNumber(6) missileCompass=input.getNumber(7)*math.pi*2 missileTiltSensorForward=input.getNumber(8)*math.pi*2 missileTiltSensorUp=input.getNumber(9)*math.pi*2 missileTiltSensorLeft=input.getNumber(10)*math.pi*2 constantPitchGain=input.getNumber(11) constantYawGain=input.getNumber(12) tickDelayCompensation=input.getNumber(13) missileFired=input.getBool(1)
--Target XYZ cartesianRotate1=math.atan(math.sin(missileTiltSensorLeft),math.sin(missileTiltSensorUp)) cartesianRotate2=missileRadarYawAngle*math.sin(cartesianRotate1)+missileRadarPitchAngle*math.cos(cartesianRotate1)+missileTiltSensorForward cartesianRotate3=(missileRadarYawAngle*math.cos(cartesianRotate1)-missileRadarPitchAngle*math.sin(cartesianRotate1)+missileCompass)*-1 targetRelativeAltitude=math.sin(cartesianRotate2)*missileRadarDistance targetRelativeZY=math.cos(cartesianRotate2)*missileRadarDistance targetRelativeX=math.sin(cartesianRotate3)*targetRelativeZY targetRelativeY=math.cos(cartesianRotate3)*targetRelativeZY targetGPSX=targetRelativeX+missileGPSX targetGPSY=targetRelativeY+missileGPSY targetAltitude=targetRelativeAltitude+missileAltitude targetcoords={targetGPSX,targetGPSY,targetAltitude} missilecoords={missileGPSX,missileGPSY,missileAltitude}
--Lin Extrapolate lasttargetcoords1=targetcoords delta=subtract_vectors(targetcoords,lasttargetcoords1) lastDelta=delta deltadelta=subtract_vectors(delta,lastDelta) targetcoords=linearExtrapolate(targetcoords,tickDelayCompensation)
grid_displacement={targetcoords[1]-missilecoords[1],targetcoords[2]-missilecoords[2],targetcoords[3]-missilecoords[3]} closing_velocity=-vector_magnitude(subtract_vectors(targetcoords,lasttargetcoords),subtract_vectors(missilecoords,lastmissilecoords)) distance=vector_magnitude(missilecoords,targetcoords) vertical_los=math.atan(grid_displacement[3]/(grid_displacement[1]^2+grid_displacement[2]^2)^.5) horizontal_los=math.atan(grid_displacement[2]/grid_displacement[1]) delta_vlos=vertical_los-last_vertical_los delta_hlos=horizontal_los-last_horizontal_los acceleration_vlos=delta_vlos-delta_delta_vlos acceleration_hlos=delta_hlos-delta_delta_hlos
--APN if missileFired then pitch=constantPitchGain*delta_vlos*closing_velocity+constantPitchGain*acceleration_vlos+vlos_jerk_pitch_gain yaw=constantYawGain*delta_hlos*closing_velocity+constantYawGain*acceleration_hlos+hlos_jerk_yaw_gain else pitch=0 yaw=0 end
output.setNumber(1,pitch) output.setNumber(2,yaw) output.setNumber(3,targetGPSX) output.setNumber(4,targetGPSY) output.setNumber(5,targetAltitude) output.setBool(1,missileFired)
delta_delta_vlos=delta_vlos delta_delta_hlos=delta_hlos last_horizontal_los=horizontal_los last_vertical_los=vertical_los lasttargetcoords=targetcoords lastmissilecoords=missilecoords
--EPN acceleration_vlos_delta = acceleration_vlos - last_acceleration_vlos last_acceleration_vlos = acceleration_vlos vlos_jerk = acceleration_vlos_delta vlos_jerk_pitch_gain = vlos_jerk * constantPitchGain
acceleration_hlos_delta = acceleration_hlos - last_acceleration_hlos last_acceleration_hlos = acceleration_hlos hlos_jerk = acceleration_hlos_delta hlos_jerk_yaw_gain = hlos_jerk * constantYawGain end
function vector_magnitude(a,b) return((a[1]-b[1])^2+(a[2]-b[2])^2+(a[3]-b[3])^2)^.5 end
function subtract_vectors(c,b)return{c[1]-b[1],c[2]-b[2],c[3]-b[3]} end
function linearExtrapolate(d,e)return{d[1]+(delta[1]+deltadelta[1])*e,d[2]+(delta[2]+deltadelta[2])*e,d[3]+(delta[3]+deltadelta[3])*e}end

function lerp(a,b,t) return a*(1-t)+b*t end function clamp(x,a,b) return math.min(math.max(x,a),b) end
function onTick() missileRadarDistance = input.getNumber(1) maxdis = 1000 constantzero = 155 constantmaxdis = 155 constant = lerp(constantzero ,constantmaxdis, clamp(missileRadarDistance/maxdis,0,1) ) --do the lerp output.setNumber(1,constant) end

M=math si=M.sin co=M.cos atan=M.atan pi=M.pi pi2=pi*2 sqrt = M.sqrt
function onTick() radarPitch = input.getNumber(1) * pi2 radarYaw = input.getNumber(2) *-1* pi2 TargetDistance = input.getNumber(3) yaw = input.getNumber(4) *-1* pi2 tiltForward = input.getNumber(5) *-1* pi2 tiltLeft = input.getNumber(6) * pi2 tiltUpForward = input.getNumber(7) * pi2 cX = input.getNumber(8) cY = input.getNumber(9) cZ = input.getNumber(10)
globalRoll = atan(si(tiltLeft), si(tiltUpForward))
adjustedRadarPitch = (radarYaw * si(globalRoll)) + (radarPitch * co(globalRoll)) adjustedRadarYaw = (radarYaw * co(globalRoll)) - (radarPitch * si(globalRoll)) finalRadarPitch = adjustedRadarPitch - tiltForward finalRadarYaw = (adjustedRadarYaw + yaw) * 1
tZ = (si(finalRadarPitch) * TargetDistance) + cZ distanceXY = co(finalRadarPitch) * TargetDistance tX = (si(finalRadarYaw) * distanceXY) + cX tY = (co(finalRadarYaw) * distanceXY) + cY
output.setNumber(1, tX) output.setNumber(2, tY) output.setNumber(3, tZ) output.setNumber(4, radarPitch)
end

end
